<subSubSection id="55CE651FFFD8FFDCD3DAFF77FDB94033" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1D6B3694FFD8FFDCD3DAFF77FA8541A4" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD3DAFF77FEE241C1" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic epithet 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD125FF77FD4941C1" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[568,741,151,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD125FF77FD4941C1" box="[568,741,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the combination of 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD79DFF78FB6641DE" box="[1152,1226,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orient</emphasis>
(from Latin noun, 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD38AFF5EFF4F41A4" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1932" box="[151,227,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Oriens" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD38AFF5EFF4F41A4" box="[151,227,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Oriens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) meaning the East with 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD2E9FF5BFE5541A4" bold="true" box="[500,505,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">'</emphasis>
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD2E4FF5CFDE241A4" box="[505,590,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gidiella</emphasis>
ꞌ a part of the closely related genus 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD0FCFF5CFBF941A4" authorityName="Hertzog" authorityYear="1933" box="[993,1109,188,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD0FCFF5CFBF941A4" box="[993,1109,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Bogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D6B3694FFD8FFDCD3DAFF01FDB94033" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD3DAFF01FD7D418B" bold="true" box="[199,721,225,250]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Composition and geographic distribution.</emphasis>
Both 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD039FF01FEE3406F" authority="(Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli, 2006)" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD039FF01FB8A418B" box="[804,1062,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD721FF01FEE4406F" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli, 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD245FEE5FE10406C" box="[344,444,261,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD2EBFEE5FCAD406F" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[502,769,261,286]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD2EBFEE5FCAD406F" box="[502,769,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD017FEE5FCE7406F" box="[778,843,261,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD017FEE5FCE7406F" bold="true" box="[778,843,261,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
inhabit the freshwater subterranean environment of the southeastern Indian peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55CE651FFFD8FFDCD3DAFEADFCF643D8" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1D6B3694FFD8FFDCD3DAFEADFCF643D8" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD3DAFEADFE974017" bold="true" box="[199,315,333,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Remarks.</emphasis>
In a previous publication, 
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD19AFEADFC2B4017" author="Sidorov, D. A. &amp; Katz, A. D. &amp; Taylor, S. J. &amp; Chertoprud, M. V." box="[647,903,333,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="23 - 43" refId="ref12434" refString="Sidorov, D. A., Katz, A. D., Taylor, S. J. &amp; Chertoprud, M. V. (2016) A reassessment of the phylogenetic utility of genus-level morphological characters in the family Bogidiellidae (Crustacea, Amphipoda), with description of a new species of Eobogidiella Karaman, 1981. ZooKeys, 610, 23 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 610.9100" type="journal article" year="2016">
Sidorov 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD1F0FEAEFC894017" box="[749,805,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, being of the opinion that 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD7C9FEADFA374017" authorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" authorityYear="2006" box="[1236,1435,333,358]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD7C9FEADFA374017" box="[1236,1435,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Bogidiella indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonged to the 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD247FE91FE4140FB" box="[346,493,369,394]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">niphargoides</emphasis>
-group, had expressed doubts about the reliability of the morphological features proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD23AFE75FD8C40DF" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." box="[295,544,405,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">
Holsinger 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD281FE76FE6040DF" box="[412,460,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">et al</emphasis>
. (2006
</bibRefCitation>
: 53), i.e. reckoning the special structural features of pereopod V for designating the 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD3DFFE59FEA440A3" authorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" authorityYear="2006" box="[194,264,441,466]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD3DFFE59FEA440A3" box="[194,264,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group (group E). However, having carried out a comparative morphological analysis of 114 described bogidiellid species in 37 genera, and in particular for 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD1F2FE3EFCF84087" authorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" authorityYear="2006" box="[751,852,477,502]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD1F2FE3EFCF84087" box="[751,852,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">B. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the former monotypic representative of the 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD651FE3DFA3E4087" authorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" authorityYear="2006" box="[1356,1426,477,502]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD651FE3DFA3E4087" box="[1356,1426,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group) versus 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD258FDE1FDF8436B" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[325,596,513,538]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta" status="gen. n., sp. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD258FDE1FDF8436B" box="[325,596,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD17FFDE1FCBE436B" box="[610,786,513,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD17FFDE1FD14436B" bold="true" box="[610,696,513,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gen. n.</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD1D1FDE1FCBE436B" bold="true" box="[716,786,513,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described herein, we agree with the rationale of the taxonomic criteria suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD115FDC5FCA7434F" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." box="[520,779,549,574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">
Holsinger 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD162FDC6FD1D434F" box="[639,689,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
for the 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD07AFDC5FC01434F" authorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" authorityYear="2006" box="[871,941,549,574]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD07AFDC5FC01434F" box="[871,941,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group of species. Based on the structurally unique pereopod V of this group, we propose here a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD091FDA9FB954313" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[908,1081,585,610]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD091FDA9FB954313" box="[908,1081,585,610]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD75FFDA9FB3F4313" box="[1090,1171,585,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD75FFDA9FB3F4313" bold="true" box="[1090,1171,585,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, to accommodate both species. This taxonomic decision warrants a new combination for nomenclatural consistency: 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD7F2FD8DFD5E43DB" authority="(Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli, 2006)" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD7F2FD8DFF7143DB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD3F6FD71FD4643DB" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." box="[235,746,657,682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">Holsinger, Ranga Reddy, and Messouli, 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD1E4FD71FCF643D8" box="[761,858,657,682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55CE651FFFD8FFDCD3DAFD55FB6142D7" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="1D6B3694FFD8FFDCD3DAFD55FB6142D7" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD3DAFD55FED843BF" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,372,693,718]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD3DAFD55FED843BF" box="[199,372,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD266FD55FE6743BF" box="[379,459,693,718]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD266FD55FE6743BF" bold="true" box="[379,459,693,718]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distributed in the coastal belt along the Eastern Ghats (Ghats orientales) at altitudes ranging from ca. 
<quantity id="DA2C9B71FFD8FFDCD240FD3AFE454380" box="[349,489,730,754]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.645" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="0.19" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" unit="m" value="364.5" valueMax="710.0" valueMin="19.0">19 to 710 m</quantity>
above sea level. Taking into account the Chidambaram specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD7E3FD39FADE4383" authorityName="Hertzog" authorityYear="1933" box="[1278,1394,729,754]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Bogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD7E3FD39FADE4383" box="[1278,1394,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Bogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD3C1FD1DFE734267" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." box="[220,479,765,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">
Holsinger 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD24FFD1EFE2F4267" box="[338,387,765,790]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, which belongs to the same genus, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD721FD1DFB454267" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[1084,1257,765,790]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD721FD1DFB454267" box="[1084,1257,765,790]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD7EDFD1DFA924267" box="[1264,1342,765,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD7EDFD1DFA924267" bold="true" box="[1264,1342,765,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
extends from 18° N l. towards the south 11° N l. exclusively along the present coastline, but not extending deeper than 
<quantity id="DA2C9B71FFD8FFDCD66FFCC2FF17422F" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
into the interior of the continent (see also discussion in 
<bibRefCitation id="79454B65FFD8FFDCD02DFCA5FB8D422F" author="Holsinger, J. R. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M." box="[816,1057,837,862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref11495" refString="Holsinger, J. R., Ranga Reddy, Y. &amp; Messouli, M. (2006) Bogidiella indica, a new species of subterranean Amphipod Crustacean (Bogidiellidae) from wells in Southeastern India, with remarks on the biogeographic importance of recently discovered bogidiellids on the Indian subcontinent. Subterranean Biology, 4, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">
Holsinger 
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD0B8FCA6FC7A422F" box="[933,982,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
). Although, we could not confirm our findings with molecular data, we are of the opinion that the species of 
<taxonomicName id="DAD44D17FFD8FFDCD0FEFC89FB3C42F3" authority="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik, 2018" authorityName="Sidorov &amp; Reddy &amp; Shaik" authorityYear="2018" box="[995,1168,873,898]" class="Malacostraca" family="Austroniphargidae" genus="Orientogidiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD0FEFC89FB3C42F3" box="[995,1168,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">Orientogidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="349357FDFFD8FFDCD78AFC89FB4B42F3" box="[1175,1255,873,898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2FA0EA86FFD8FFDCD78AFC89FB4B42F3" bold="true" box="[1175,1255,873,898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, sharing unique phenotypic features, inhabit a common territory along the east coast of 
<collectingCountry id="65C37604FFD8FFDCD0A8FC6DFC4342D7" box="[949,1007,909,934]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="406">India</collectingCountry>
for about 
<quantity id="DA2C9B71FFD8FFDCD77FFC6EFB6442D7" box="[1122,1224,909,934]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="406" unit="km" value="1000.0">1000 km</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
